1 MY faith looks up to thee ,
Now hear me while I pray ;
Oh let me from this day
As thou hast died for me ,
Oh ! may my love to thee ,
As thou hast died for me , Oh ! may my love to thee , Pure , warm , and changeless be , A living fire .
3 While life's dark maze I tread ,
Bid darkness turn to day , Wipe sorrow's tears away , Nor let me ever stray
Fear and distrust remove : Oh ! bear me . safe above- A ransomed soul .
1 " GLORY to God on high ! " Let heaven and earth reply , Praise ye his name ! " ⁹ His love and grace adore , Who all our sorrows bore ; Sing aloud evermore-
2 Ye who surround the throne , Cheerfully join in one , Praising his name :
Our Lord and God to bless ;
On him we fix our choice ,
3 Join all ye ransomed race Our Lord and God to bless ; Praise ye his name : On him we fix our choice , In him we will rejoice , Shouting with heart and voice- " Worthy the Lamb . "
4 Soon must we close our race ,
4 Soon must we close our race , Yet will we never cease Praising his name :
But as we upward wing , Hail him our gracious King , And through the heavens sing- " Worthy the Lamb . "
